# Next.js — Components & UI (Part 3)

## 17. Custom Hooks

Business logic in hooks. `use` prefix; keep pure and testable. Example `useDebounce`:

```ts
export function useDebounce<T>(value: T, delay = 300) {
  const [debounced, setDebounced] = useState(value)
  useEffect(() => {
    const t = setTimeout(() => setDebounced(value), delay)
    return () => clearTimeout(t)
  }, [value, delay])
  return debounced
}
```

## 18. Component Guidelines

- Functional components; single responsibility; < 200 LOC.
- Semantic elements; stable `key` for lists; prefer `forwardRef` when ref needed.
- Client Components only when interactivity required; Server when possible.

## 19. Reusable Components

Place in `shared/components/`. Variants via props. Use `forwardRef` when exposing DOM ref:

```tsx
export const Input = forwardRef<HTMLInputElement, InputProps>(
  (props, ref) => <input ref={ref} {...props} />
)
```

## 19a. cn() / tailwind-merge

```ts
// shared/utils/cn.ts
import { clsx } from 'clsx'
import { twMerge } from 'tailwind-merge'
export const cn = (...inputs: ClassValue[]) => twMerge(clsx(inputs))
```

Use to merge and override Tailwind classes.

## 19b. Error Boundary Component

Shared `ErrorFallback` for `error.tsx`. Use `react-error-boundary` with retry.

## 20. Loading & Skeleton

Match skeleton layout to content to avoid CLS.

## 21. Toast / Notification

Provider (sonner, react-hot-toast). Call from sagas/interceptors.

## 22. Layout Primitives

PageLayout, Header, Sidebar, Footer in `shared/components/layout/`.

## 23. Empty State

Dedicated component for no-data / no-results.

## 24. Context Usage

Theme, locale. Avoid for server data. Keep value stable (memoize).

## 25. Compound Components

Modal.Header, Modal.Body, Modal.Footer with implicit context.

## 26. Utils Structure

`shared/utils/`: `format.ts`, `cn.ts`, `storage.ts`, `index.ts` barrel.

## 27. CSS & Styling

- **Tailwind**: content paths in config; `@tailwind` in `globals.css`.
- **Design tokens**: colors, spacing, radii in `tailwind.config.js` or CSS vars.
- **Z-index scale**: `--z-dropdown`, `--z-modal`, `--z-toast`.
- **Conventions**: Prefer utilities over `@apply`; use `cn()` (clsx + twMerge); avoid arbitrary values when token exists.
- **CSS Modules**: `.module.css` for scoped styles.
